      "content": "The French Revolution, ignited in 1789 amid widespread discontent, fundamentally transformed France’s social and political landscape. The Storming of the Bastille on July 14 became a symbolic key event, initiating a decade-long upheaval. It unfolded amidst the Reign of Terror, where radical revolutionaries, led by figures such as Maximilien Robespierre, targeted perceived enemies, resulting in thousands, including King Louis XVI, facing their demise. This period also saw influential voices, like Jean-Paul Marat and Madame Roland, fall victim to the revolution's extreme measures. By Napoleon Bonaparte's rise to control in the late 1790s, the revolution had radically redefined France's course, creating a power vacuum that Bonaparte swiftly capitalized on.",
